# Introduction Tour

The Introduction component (`client/src/components/Introduction.tsx`) is a spotlight-style guided tour shown to first-time users. It highlights actual UI elements and positions tooltips next to them. It must stay in sync with the application's feature set.

## When to update

- **New UI feature or page**: Add a `data-tour="<name>"` attribute to the key element in the component's JSX, then add a step to the `STEPS` array in `Introduction.tsx` with a `selector` pointing to that attribute.
- **Renamed or removed feature**: Update or remove the corresponding step and `data-tour` attribute.
- **Changed navigation or layout**: Update step `position` values if the element moved to a different area of the screen.

## Step format

Each step in the `STEPS` array has:
- `title`: Short feature name (e.g. "Play Online", "Puzzle Trainer")
- `selector`: CSS selector targeting a `data-tour` attribute on the element to highlight (e.g. `[data-tour='nav-play']`). Omit for centered modal steps (welcome/intro).
- `position`: Where the tooltip appears relative to the highlighted element: `"bottom"`, `"top"`, `"left"`, or `"right"`
- `content`: JSX with `<p>` tags explaining the feature. Use `<strong>` for UI element names.

## Data-tour attributes

Add `data-tour="<name>"` to the outermost DOM element of any feature that should be highlighted. Existing attributes:
- `nav-play`, `nav-computer`, `nav-puzzles`, `nav-games` — NavBar links
- `online-count` — Live Socket.IO connection count in NavBar (next to settings; appears after first count; intro step omitted when `FEATURE_ONLINE_PLAYER_COUNT=false`)
- `settings-btn` — Board settings gear icon in NavBar
- `time-grid` — Time control preset grid in Lobby
- `rooms-table` — Open games table in Lobby
- `private-game` — "Create Private Game" button in Lobby

## Rules

- Keep the step order logical: language picker → welcome → core gameplay features visible on lobby → nav links for other pages → customization.
- First step (language picker) and second step (welcome) have no `selector` — they render as centered modals.
- After adding/removing a step, update `introduction.test.ts` (default 12 steps with all features; 10 when both optional NavBar features are off).
